<body>
    <h1>Introduction to MERN Stack</h1>

    <p>
        The <strong>MERN stack</strong> is a popular set of technologies used for building full-stack JavaScript applications. 
        It combines <strong>MongoDB</strong>, <strong>Express.js</strong>, <strong>React</strong>, and <strong>Node.js</strong> to enable efficient development of modern web applications. 
    </p>

    <ol>
        <li>MongoDB – NoSQL database used for storing application data.</li>
        <li>Express.js – Lightweight framework for building server-side applications in Node.</li>
        <li>React – Front-end JavaScript library for building user interfaces.</li>
        <li>Node.js – JavaScript runtime environment for executing code on the server.</li>
    </ol>

    <img src="https://via.placeholder.com/600x300?text=MERN+Stack" alt="MERN Stack Diagram">

    <p>
        Learn more about <a href="https://www.mongodb.com/" target="_blank">MongoDB</a>.
    </p>
